# Gradle Build Conventions

## Multi-Module Structure
```
speleoDB_plugin/                       (root project)
├── com.arianesline.ariane.plugin.api/ (git submodule - plugin API interfaces)
├── com.arianesline.cavelib.api/       (git submodule - cave survey data model)
├── org.speleodb.ariane.plugin.speleodb/ (git submodule - the actual plugin)
└── com.arianesline.plugincontainer/   (local dev runner with JavaFX host)
```

## Versioning
- CalVer format: `YYYY.MM.DD` (e.g., `2026.03.25`)
- `generateReleaseVersion` task mutates `SpeleoDBConstants.java` to inject VERSION
- `settings.gradle` FlowAction resets VERSION to `null` and TEST_MODE to `false` after build

## Build vs Test
- `build` task is overridden to only depend on `assemble` (no tests)
- Run tests explicitly: `./gradlew test` or `./gradlew check`
- `enableTestMode` task sets `TEST_MODE = true` in source before test compilation
- CI must run `./gradlew build test` to actually execute tests

## Dependencies
- Root `subprojects {}` block applies: java-library, javafx plugin, Java 21, `-Xlint:all`
- Plugin module has: Jakarta JSON, JAXB, JUnit 5, AssertJ, Mockito, TestFX
- Plugin container shares Jakarta JSON + JAXB but no test deps

## JAR Packaging
- `archiveBaseName = 'org.speleodb.ariane.plugin.speleodb'`
- CalVer version in filename
- DEFLATED compression, ZIP64, sealed manifest
- `compileJava { options.debug = false }` for release builds (no debug symbols)

## Tasks
- `copyPlugin`: copies built JAR to plugincontainer's `plugins/` folder
- `copyAndRun`: copies plugin JAR then runs the container
- `resetSuccessGifPreference`: utility to reset user preference
